Clusters of prices vs height: Outliers search¶

In [139]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 7))

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
est = KMeans(n_clusters=5)
est.fit(data[['list_price','height']])
labels = est.labels_

colors_labels = labels.astype(np.float)
plt.scatter(data['list_price'],data['height'], c=colors_labels)

Clusters of prices vs 'height and width': Tier classification¶

In [161]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

data = data[data_original['height']<60]
data = data[data_original['width']<60]


fig = plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))
ax = Axes3D(fig)

classification = KMeans(n_clusters=5)
classification.fit(data[['list_price','width','height']])
labels = classification.labels_

colors_labels = labels.astype(np.float)
ax.scatter(data['width'],data['height'],data['list_price'], c=labels.astype(np.float))
